7 - git subprocess for branch deletion.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. `sort.Strings` in Production Set Deduplication (Should Use `slices.Sorted(maps.Keys(...))`)\\n\\n**`/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go`** lines 577-593:\\n```go\\nseen := make(map[string]bool)\\n...\\nsort.Strings(result)\\nreturn result\\n```\\nThis pattern of iterating over a map, collecting unique values in a slice, and then sorting is done repeatedly across the codebase. With Go 1.23, `slices.Sorted(maps.Keys(m))` handles this in one line - but `maps` is not imported anywhere in the project.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. `for i := 0; i < len(x); i++` Loop Style (Should Use Range)\\n\\n**`/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go`** line 1097:\\n```go\\nfor i := 0; i < len(entries); i++ {\\n```\\nThis particular loop is justified (it manually advances `i` for rename entries), but it is worth calling out. The overall pattern is documented.\\n\\n**`/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/explain.go`** line 242:\\n```go\\nfor i := 0; i < len(matches) && i < 5; i++ {\\n```\\nThis could be replaced with `for i, m := range matches[:min(5, len(matches))]` or using the builtin `min`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7. `string([]byte)` Conversions That Could Be Avoided\\n\\nMany places read bytes from OS/git commands and then immediately convert to string for `strings.*` operations. This is idiomatic Go, but notable hot-path instances exist:\\n\\n**`/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go`** line 1095:\\n```go\\nentries := strings.Split(string(output), \\\"\\\\x00\\\")\\n```\\nThis could use `bytes.Split(output, []byte(\\\"\\\\x00\\\"))` to avoid the allocation.\\n\\n**`/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/chunking.go`** lines 76, 170:\\n```go\\nlines := strings.Split(string(content), \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\ntrimmed := strings.TrimSpace(string(content))\\n```\\nCould use `bytes.Split` and `bytes.TrimSpace`.\\n\\n**`/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/a