gy/cleanup.go`\\n- `agent/registry.go`\\n\\nA generic helper like:\\n```go\\nfunc SortedKeys[K constraints.Ordered, V any](m map[K]V) []K { ... }\\n```\\nwould eliminate this repetition. None currently exists.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 12. `errors.Is`/`errors.As` Usage is Generally Good\\n\\nError wrapping with `%w` is used consistently throughout the codebase. `errors.Is` and `errors.As` are used correctly for sentinel and typed errors. No direct type assertions (`err.(*SomeError)`) were found in error handling paths - the codebase has adopted the modern error inspection idioms.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary Table\\n\\n| Issue | Files | Priority |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| `sort.Slice`/`sort.Strings` vs `slices.SortFunc`/`slices.Sort` | 14 files, 25+ occurrences | High |\\n| `interface{}` instead of `any` | 12+ files, production types | Medium |\\n| `context.Background()` not threaded through | `strategy/`, `checkpoint/`, `session/`, `paths/` | Medium |\\n| `map[string]bool` vs `map[string]struct{}` inconsistency | 20+ files | Low-Medium |\\n| `maps` package never used | All of codebase | Low |\\n| `string([]byte)` before `strings.*` calls on hot paths | `chunking.go`, `hooks.go`, `temporary.go` | Low |\\n| `errors.New` vs `fmt.Errorf` for non-wrapping | `interactive.go` | Low |\\n| `sync.RWMutex` manual cache (vs `sync.Map`) | `paths/paths.go` | Low |\\n| No generic helpers for set/dedup/sort | All of codebase | Low |\\n| Old-style `for i := 0; i < len(x)` loops | `temporary.go`, `explain.go` | Low |\"}],\"totalDurationMs\":220534,\"totalTokens\":97390,\"totalToolUseCount\":83,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1101,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":90558,\"output_tokens\":5730,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1101,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"44c