ire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/stringutil/stringutil_test.go` — 3 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trailers/trailers_test.go` — 8 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/messages_test.go` — 7 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent_test.go` — 5 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/session_test.go` — 6 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry_test.go` — 6 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/chunking_test.go` — 12 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/backwards_compat_test.go` — 1 test, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary_test.go` — 6 tests, no global state (uses `t.TempDir()`, not `t.Chdir`)\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id/id_test.go` — 4 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/logging/context_test.go` — 9 tests, no global state\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/commit_message_test.go` — 2 tests, no global state\\n\\n**Subtests inside `t.Run()` also missing `t.Parallel()`** — `tparallel` linter is enabled but `presets: comments` in exclusions may suppress some of these:\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/status_test.go:196` — subtest in table-driven test at `TestTimeAgo`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/versioncheck/versioncheck_test.go:43` — subtest at `TestIsOutdated`\\n\\n**Note:** The following correctly omit `t.Parallel()` because they use `t.Chdir()`/`t.Setenv()`:\\n`config_test.go`, `clean_test.go`, `state_test.go`, `reset_test.go`, `resume_test.go`, `phase_wiring_test.go`, `logging/logger_test.go`, `strategy/auto_commit_test.go`, `strategy/manual_commit_staging_test.go`, etc.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. Duplicate `DefaultStrategyName` Constant\\n\\nTwo packages define the same constant independently:\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go:19`: `const DefaultStrategyName = \\\"manual-commit\\\"`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/registry.go:62`: `const DefaultStrategyName = StrategyNameManualCommit`\\n\\nThe comment in `settings.go` acknowledges this duplication (\\\"This is duplicated here to avoid importing the strategy package (which would create a cycle)\\\"). However, this means there are now two sources of truth for the default strategy name. If the default ever changed, one might be missed.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. Hardcoded Strategy Name Strings in Logging Calls\\n\\nIn `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` and `strategy/manual_commit_git.go`, the string `\\\"manual-commit\\\"` is hardcoded in ~19 `slog.String(\\\"strategy\\\", \\\"manual-commit\\\")` logging calls instead of using the defined constant `StrategyNameManualCommit`:\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:225,236,264,289,308,350,362,389,439,449,589,603,739,797,899,1217`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_git.go:107,153,270`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trailers/trailers.go:208,220` — `\\\"manual-commit\\\"` hardcoded in `FormatShadowCommit` and `FormatShadowTaskCommit` instead of using the constant\\n\\nSimilarly in `strategy/auto_commit.go:148,165,536`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. Duplicated `fileExists` Helper Function\\n\\nThe same trivial helper is defined in three separate places:\\n\\n```go\\nfunc fileExists(path string) bool {\\n    _, err := os.Stat(path)\\n    return err == nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/utils.go:36`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go:829`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/common.go:990`\\n\\nSince each is in a different package and cross-package import would create cycles, this is somewhat forced. However, it should at least be documented, and a shared utility package (like `paths`) could potentially house it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. Duplicated `isAccessibleMode` / `IsAccessibleMode`\\n\\nThe accessibility check is duplicated:\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/utils.go:14`: exported `IsAccessibleMode()` in the `cli` package\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_reset.go:14`: unexported `isAccessibleMode()` in the `strategy` package — same implementation, same env var\\n\\nAgain, import cycles prevent sharing. The duplication at least has a comment in `manual_commit_reset.go`. The two function names also differ in capitalization convention (`Is` vs `is`), which is consistent with exported vs. unexported status, but worth noting.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. `os.Stderr` Usage Instead of `cmd.ErrOrStderr()`\\n\\nMultiple files write directly to `os.Stderr` rather than using the Cobra `cmd.ErrOrStderr()` or accepting an `io.Writer` parameter. This makes testing harder and is inconsistent with the CLAUDE.md pattern. Key files:\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/resume.go` — ~30+ occurrences of `fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, ...)`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — `fmt.Fprintln(os.Stderr, ...)` at lines 177, 194, 207, 212, 238, 246, 257, 271, 278, 286, 296, 303, 323, 324\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/rewind.go` — multiple `fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, ...)` at lines 207, 209, 211, 272, 281, 322-324, 432, 434, 436, 475, 523\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` — `fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, ...)`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. `fmt.Println`/`fmt.Printf` Used in Strategy Package (User-Facing Output)\\n\\nThe CLAUDE.md notes that operational messages should use the `logging` package and user-facing output should use `fmt.Fprint*(cmd.OutOrStdout(), ...)`. However, some strategy code uses bare `fmt.Print*`:\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go:438-440` — `fmt.Println()` and `fmt.Printf(\\\"Reset to commit %s\\\\n\\\", shortID)`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/hooks.go:217-218` — `fmt.Println(\\\"✓ Installed git hooks ...\\\")`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go:398-404` — `fmt.Printf(\\\"Restored files from shadow commit %s\\\\n\\\", ...)`\\n\\nThese go to stdout but don't use a writer parameter, making them untestable.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 8. Magic Number `7` for Git Short Hash Truncation\\n\\nThe literal `[:7]` appears in at least 15 places for truncating git commit hashes for display, without a named constant:\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/rewind.go:133,183,527,628,640,1029`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/status.go:261`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/explain.go:367,398,412,474,1115,1173,1416`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/resume.go:143`\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:870` — `truncateHash` hard-codes `7`\\n\\nMeanwhile `checkpointID.ShortIDLength = 12` exists as a constant. There is no equivalent `GitShortHashLength = 7` constant. The `truncateHash` function in `manual_commit_hooks.go` only exists within that file and is not shared.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 9. Duplicate `checkpointIDDisplayLength = 12` Magic Number\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/explain.go:1311`: local constant `checkpointIDDisplayLength = 12`\\n- Should use `checkpointID.ShortIDLength` from the `checkpoint/id` package, which already defines this as `ShortIDLength = 12`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 10. Potentially Unused / Dead Code: `ParseCondensation` and `CondensationTrailerKey`\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trailers/trailers.go:32,60,105-113`: `CondensationTrailerKey`, `condensationTrailerRegex`, and `ParseCondensation()` are defined\\n- `CondensationTrailerKey` appears only in one integration test checking that it's NOT present (`manual_commit_workflow_test.go:239`)\\n- `ParseCondensation()` is not called anywhere in production code or tests (only defined)\\n- These appear to be legacy code that could be removed\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 11. Deprecated `paths.CheckpointPath()` Still Called\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths/paths.go:43`: `// Deprecated: Use checkpointID.Path() directly instead.`\\n- Still called at `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go:205` with `//nolint:staticcheck // already present in codebase`\\n\\nThe nolint suppressor is correct but this should be cleaned up.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 12. Deprecated `TestEnv.Cleanup()` Called in ~39+ Test Invocations\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/testenv.go:90-106`: `Cleanup()` is marked as a no-op and deprecated\\n- Still called 14 times in `manual_commit_workflow_test.go`, 7 times in `session_conflict_test.go`, 7 times in `logs_only_rewind_test.go`, 4 times in `manual_commit_untracked_files_test.go`, etc.\\n- Total ~39+ `defer env.Cleanup()` calls that do nothing\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 13. Inconsistent Error Wrapping Pattern\\n\\nSome errors are returned bare (without wrapping), particularly:\\n\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/utils.go:45`: `return err //nolint:wrapcheck // already present in codebase` — `copyFile`'s `os.ReadFile` error is not wrapped while the `os.WriteFile` error IS wrapped with context\\n- `/Users/pfleidi/entire/cli/cmd/entire/cli/rewind.go:393`: `return fmt.Errorf(\\\"%s\\\", changeMsg)` — odd pattern; should be `errors.New(changeMsg)` (using `fmt.Errorf` without `%w` and with a static string)\\n- Multiple bare `return err` in `checkpoint/committed.go` vs. wrapped errors elsewhere in the same file\\n\\nThe `\\\"already present in codebase\\\"` nolint comment is used 21 times across the codebase as a placeholder for future cleanup across `wrapcheck`, `nilerr`, `nilnil`, `staticcheck`, `wrapcheck`, `goconst` linters.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 14. Th